An Act relative to increasing language offerings for licensure exams.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Section 87V of chapter 112 of the General Laws, as appearing in the 2022
2 Official Edition, is hereby amended by inserting after the second sentence the following
3 sentence:- The board shall offer all practical and written examinations in the following
4 languages: English, Spanish, Vietnamese, Chinese and Haitian Creole.
5 SECTION 2. Section 65 of chapter 146 of the General Laws, as so appearing, is hereby
6 amended by adding at the end thereof the following paragraph:-
7 The division of occupational licensure shall make both written and practical examinations
8 available in the languages of English and Spanish to operator of hoisting machinery applicants if
9 the criteria for licensure established by the commissioner of the division of occupational
10 licensure pursuant to section fifty-three are met by the applicant.
11 SECTION 3. Section 6B of chapter 149 of the General Laws, as so appearing, is hereby
12 amended by adding at the end thereof the following paragraph:-
1 of 2

13 The commissioner shall offer the application and examination for a license issued or
14 renewed pursuant to this section in English, Spanish and Portuguese, and may offer the
15 application and examination in any other language.
